🧩 Challenge 1: Build a Header with Navigation using React Router

🎯 Task

Create a reusable Header component and implement page navigation using `react-router-dom`

📌 Requirements

1. Header Component

* Logo + Website Title
* Navigation Menu:

  * Home
  * Courses
  * About
  * Contact
* Action Buttons:

  * Login
  * Sign Up
-------------------------------------------------------

2. Routing (Main Focus 🚀)

* Install and use `react-router-dom`

* Create separate pages/components:

  * Home.jsx
  * Courses
  * About.jsx
  * Contact.jsx

* When clicking menu items:
  👉 Navigate to respective pages without page reload
-------------------------------------------------------
3. Use Proper Components

* Use `<BrowserRouter>`, `<Routes>`, `<Route>`
* Use `<Link>` or `<NavLink>` inside Header
-------------------------------------------------------
📌 UI Layout
Header should be at the top (fixed or static)
Navigation links should be center or right-aligned
Logo + Title should be left-aligned
Page content should change below the header
Header should be visible on all pages
-------------------------------------------------------
🧪 Expected Flow
Click Home → Show Home page
Click About → Show About page
Click Contact → Show Contact page
Header remains unchanged


